<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,416,693]" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,525,549]" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</emphasis>
The material of this species is represented in the 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14844" box="[871,916,525,549]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14844" name="Scripps Institution of Oceanography" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">SIO</collectionCode>
collection by three tubes (no animals present) with three longitudinal ridges raised into curved spines. Such very distinctive tubes were recently reported by Kupriyanova &amp; Nishi (
<number box="[424,483,597,621]" pageId="8" pageNumber="51" value="2010.0">2010</number>
) for 
<taxonomicName box="[548,808,597,621]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Bathyvermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="8" pageNumber="51" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="eliasoni">
<emphasis box="[548,808,597,621]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">Bathyvermilia eliasoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Patton-Murray Seamounts, Gulf of Alaska, North-Eastern Pacific Ocean. Kupriyanova &amp; Nishi (
<number box="[747,806,633,657]" pageId="8" pageNumber="51" value="2010.0">2010</number>
) also briefly discussed the wide geographic distribution of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
